Now, we need to produce the fix for getLine. The fixed code should:

1. When there is no newline after pos, return the substring from pos to the end if pos < js.length(), otherwise return null.
2. Also ensure that the caching works correctly? The current caching might also have a bug if lastLine is not updated on null return? But the fix should be minimal, so we only fix the last line case.

So the fixed code:

```
  public String getLine(int lineNumber) {
    String js = "";
    try {
      js = getCode();
    } catch (IOException e) {
      return null;
    }

    int pos = 0;
    int startLine = 1;

    if (lineNumber >= lastLine) {
      pos = lastOffset;
      startLine = lastLine;
    }

    for (int n = startLine; n < lineNumber; n++) {
      int nextpos = js.indexOf('\n', pos);
      if (nextpos == -1) {
        return null;
      }
      pos = nextpos + 1;
    }

    lastOffset = pos;
    lastLine = lineNumber;

    int nextpos = js.indexOf('\n', pos);
    if (nextpos == -1) {
      if (pos < js.length()) {
        return js.substring(pos);
      } else {
        return null;
      }
    } else {
      return js.substring(pos, nextpos);
    }
  }
```

Note: The original used `js.indexOf('\n', pos)` twice; we store it in a variable to avoid redundant search.

